Key Match Events: Donte DiVincenzo scored 26 points as the Minnesota Timberwolves defeated the San Antonio Spurs 112-110.
Rudy Gobert had 17 points and 15 rebounds for the Timberwolves.
Julius Randle had 16 points, while Jaden McDaniels added 12 points and 10 boards for Minnesota.
Victor Wembanyama led San Antonio with 34 points and eight rebounds.
Harrison Barnes had 24 points, Devin Vassell had 22 and Chris Paul dished out 14 assists.
Victor Wembanyama missed a free throw late in the second half.
